dev/acceptance.md:384:**Assertion:** A host process whose only work is `Engine.open(); Engine.close()` exits within 5 s of `close()` returning.
dev/acceptance.md:504:**Assertion:** Calling a vector-requiring operation on an engine with no embedder configured raises typed `EmbedderNotConfigured` at the call boundary.
dev/acceptance.md:512:**Assertion:** Calling a vector operation against a kind not configured for vector indexing raises typed `KindNotVectorIndexed` at the call boundary.
dev/acceptance.md:616:**Assertion:** `fathomdb recover` is invocable via the CLI with `--help` properties per AC-040a / AC-040b; no recovery verb is reachable from the runtime SDK (Python / TypeScript) — no public symbol named `recover`, `restore_*`, `repair`, or equivalent is exposed by the five-verb application surface (REQ-053 / AC-057a).
dev/acceptance.md:617:**Measurement:** (1) Invoke `fathomdb recover --help`; assert per AC-040a / AC-040b. (2) Per binding: enumerate the public surface per AC-057a's surface definition; assert none of `{recover, restore, repair, fix, rebuild}` are members.
