1. `must-fix` [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:23), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:241), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:332), [src/python/tests/test_ffi_safety.py](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/python/tests/test_ffi_safety.py:19)  
   Panic handling does not satisfy AC-067. The binding deliberately translates unwinds to `EngineError`, not `pyo3::panic::PanicException` or a subclass of it: the module docs say so, `call_engine()` returns `EngineError::new_err(...)` on unwind, `open()` does the same, and the Python test only asserts `BaseException`. The accepted contract is a `PanicException`-class exception without process abort.

2. `must-fix` [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/Cargo.toml](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/Cargo.toml:14), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:531)  
   `force_panic_for_test()` is not effectively release-gated. The crate enables `test-hooks` in default features, so a normal build exports the test hook unless the build explicitly disables defaults. The prompt requires the hook to exist only under `#[cfg(any(test, feature = "test-hooks"))]` and not ship in release wheels.

3. `must-fix` [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:115)  
   Error mapping collapses distinct engine variants into generic Python classes. `EmbedderNotConfigured` maps to `EmbedderError`, and `KindNotVectorIndexed` maps to `VectorError`. That violates the binding rule of one concrete class per variant and fails AC-060a’s typed-dispatch contract.

4. `should-fix` [src/python/tests/test_surface.py](/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/src/python/tests/test_surface.py:1)  
   The review prompt asked for AC-bound coverage including AC-057a, but `test_surface.py` does not cite AC-057a anywhere. The surface test exists, but the acceptance binding is implicit rather than explicit.

